<p>Create a nice and readable function:</p>

<pre><code>def range_with_negatives(start, end):
    for x in range(start, end):
        yield x
        yield -x
</code></pre>

<p>Usage:</p>

<pre><code>list(range_with_negatives(6, 10))
</code></pre>

<p>That is how you get a convenient one-liner for anything. Avoid trying to look like a magic pro hacker.</p>
